1
00:00:01,353 --> 00:00:08,543
♪

2
00:00:08,543 --> 00:00:11,543
(singing in foreign language)

3
00:00:11,543 --> 00:01:44,563
♪

4
00:01:50,789 --> 00:01:52,789
(rapid firing)

5
00:01:52,789 --> 00:01:56,639
♪

6
00:01:56,639 --> 00:01:57,629
What is it?

7
00:01:57,629 --> 00:01:59,639
His speed's the same,
but he's different.

8
00:01:59,639 --> 00:02:00,669
It's his attitude.

9
00:02:00,669 --> 00:02:02,619
He's never been like this.

10
00:02:02,619 --> 00:02:03,689
So intense.

11
00:02:03,689 --> 00:02:05,759
There's a truth I have
accepted all these years.

12
00:02:05,759 --> 00:02:07,619
If you're strong, you live.

13
00:02:07,619 --> 00:02:10,649
If you're weak, you die.

14
00:02:10,649 --> 00:02:13,579
It's a simple philosophy
Mr. Shishio taught me,

15
00:02:13,579 --> 00:02:15,619
along with my sword technique,

16
00:02:15,619 --> 00:02:18,499
and it has protected me.

17
00:02:18,499 --> 00:02:22,549
It is my strength of will
that'll defeat Kenshin.

18
00:02:22,549 --> 00:02:23,709
You're wrong about me.

19
00:02:23,709 --> 00:02:25,759
I have no doubts,
and I'll prove it.

20
00:02:25,759 --> 00:02:27,759
♪

21
00:02:27,759 --> 00:02:29,569
He's letting his emotions show.

22
00:02:29,569 --> 00:02:30,769
Kenshin can read his moves.

23
00:02:30,769 --> 00:02:31,709
Sojiro.

24
00:02:31,709 --> 00:02:34,719
♪

25
00:02:34,719 --> 00:02:36,549
He's lost.

26
00:02:36,549 --> 00:02:37,779
♪

27
00:02:44,549 --> 00:02:46,769
Why are you hesitating, Himura?

28
00:02:46,769 --> 00:02:50,549
Let's face it, you can't win
unless you've finished me off.

29
00:02:53,659 --> 00:02:56,599
I don't wanna hurt you,
and you know what?

30
00:02:56,599 --> 00:02:58,699
I don't think that you
wanna hurt me either, really.

31
00:02:58,699 --> 00:03:00,639
You try to cover it up,

32
00:03:00,639 --> 00:03:02,529
but underneath all that bluster,

33
00:03:02,529 --> 00:03:04,749
I think you're just
a scared little kid.

34
00:03:04,749 --> 00:03:06,529
Bullies like you aren't born,

35
00:03:06,529 --> 00:03:08,559
they're made.

36
00:03:08,559 --> 00:03:09,669
I can see you've been influenced

37
00:03:09,669 --> 00:03:10,789
by the wrong teacher,

38
00:03:10,789 --> 00:03:12,579
but it's not too late.

39
00:03:14,519 --> 00:03:16,619
If you wanna change, I can help.

40
00:03:16,619 --> 00:03:18,669
Just try to keep an open mind.

41
00:03:18,669 --> 00:03:22,659
First you have to accept
that you're on the wrong path.

42
00:03:22,659 --> 00:03:25,639
Then you have
to face your fears.

43
00:03:25,639 --> 00:03:27,709
You've used your
anger as a weapon,

44
00:03:27,709 --> 00:03:29,529
when, in fact, you never really

45
00:03:29,529 --> 00:03:31,539
wanted to hurt anyone
in the first place.

46
00:03:32,729 --> 00:03:35,659
Sojiro, am I getting
through to you?

47
00:03:35,659 --> 00:03:36,699
Sojiro?

48
00:03:36,699 --> 00:03:38,669
(rain falling)

49
00:03:41,629 --> 00:03:43,649
If you're strong, you live.

50
00:03:45,619 --> 00:03:47,679
And if you're weak, you die.

51
00:03:47,679 --> 00:03:49,519
Is it possible that this lesson,

52
00:03:49,519 --> 00:03:52,549
which is the basis
of Mr. Shishio's philosophy,

53
00:03:52,549 --> 00:03:54,569
isn't really true?

54
00:03:56,769 --> 00:03:58,719
According to my sensei,

55
00:03:58,719 --> 00:04:01,589
any uncertainty or sympathy
when facing an opponent

56
00:04:01,589 --> 00:04:03,679
is a fatal error.

57
00:04:03,679 --> 00:04:06,599
That's why I never
questioned any of his orders

58
00:04:06,599 --> 00:04:09,599
and just carried
out my missions.

59
00:04:09,599 --> 00:04:11,579
The truth is, though,

60
00:04:11,579 --> 00:04:13,759
Himura's right.

61
00:04:13,759 --> 00:04:16,659
I killed people when
I didn't really want to.

62
00:04:16,659 --> 00:04:18,629
But I can't stop now.

63
00:04:18,629 --> 00:04:21,529
I have nowhere to go
and nobody to guide me.

64
00:04:27,609 --> 00:04:28,719
How can I function?

65
00:04:28,719 --> 00:04:32,609
I feel like I'm being
ripped in half by two horses.

66
00:04:32,609 --> 00:04:34,609
(screaming)

67
00:04:34,609 --> 00:04:44,649
♪

68
00:04:44,649 --> 00:04:46,519
Sojiro.

69
00:04:46,519 --> 00:04:47,769
He's falling apart.

70
00:04:47,769 --> 00:04:49,769
(crying)

71
00:04:49,769 --> 00:05:00,519
♪

72
00:05:00,519 --> 00:05:01,549
I reject you!

73
00:05:01,549 --> 00:05:05,789
♪

74
00:05:05,789 --> 00:05:07,619
I know your game.

75
00:05:07,619 --> 00:05:09,609
♪

76
00:05:09,609 --> 00:05:13,559
You're trying
to confuse me.

77
00:05:13,559 --> 00:05:14,789
You know I can beat you

78
00:05:14,789 --> 00:05:16,569
so you're messin' with my head,

79
00:05:16,569 --> 00:05:18,669
hoping I'll slip up
and make a mistake.

80
00:05:18,669 --> 00:05:20,649
It's not gonna work,
I see through your plan.

81
00:05:20,649 --> 00:05:22,659
♪

82
00:05:22,659 --> 00:05:23,699
You almost had me fooled.

83
00:05:23,699 --> 00:05:24,769
Very smart.

84
00:05:24,769 --> 00:05:27,629
(panting)

85
00:05:27,629 --> 00:05:29,669
Now, no matter what you say,
I'm gonna kill you.

86
00:05:29,669 --> 00:05:41,789
♪

87
00:05:41,789 --> 00:05:43,579
You ready to die?

88
00:05:43,579 --> 00:05:47,719
♪

89
00:05:47,719 --> 00:05:48,669
This is it.

90
00:05:48,669 --> 00:05:49,679
Say goodbye.

91
00:05:49,679 --> 00:05:50,689
Your time is up.

92
00:05:50,689 --> 00:05:55,649
♪

93
00:05:55,649 --> 00:05:57,719
I sure hope Kenshin
can handle him.

94
00:05:57,719 --> 00:06:00,549
This boy has
an unorthodox technique,

95
00:06:00,549 --> 00:06:01,769
but more than that
I'm very concerned

96
00:06:01,769 --> 00:06:03,579
about his lightning speed.

97
00:06:03,579 --> 00:06:06,629
I'm going to take pity
on you, Mr. Himura.

98
00:06:06,629 --> 00:06:08,749
I'm going to kill you fast.

99
00:06:08,749 --> 00:06:11,539
I'll use my
Quick Heaven technique.

100
00:06:11,539 --> 00:06:13,779
I assure you,
you won't feel any pain.

101
00:06:13,779 --> 00:06:15,589
How polite of you, Sojiro.

102
00:06:15,589 --> 00:06:17,569
I suppose you
expect me to thank you,

103
00:06:17,569 --> 00:06:18,779
but you'll pardon me if I don't.

104
00:06:18,779 --> 00:06:20,659
You see, I have
a plan of my own,

105
00:06:20,659 --> 00:06:22,749
and it doesn't involve my death.

106
00:06:22,749 --> 00:06:25,759
In fact, I'm even wondering
if you can carry out your plan,

107
00:06:25,759 --> 00:06:28,519
considering how well
you'll need to perform.

108
00:06:28,519 --> 00:06:30,499
I don't plan to just
stand here, ya know.

109
00:06:30,499 --> 00:06:31,609
Yeah, so what?

110
00:06:31,609 --> 00:06:32,669
I'm not worried.

111
00:06:32,669 --> 00:06:34,509
Whether you fight or not,

112
00:06:34,509 --> 00:06:35,749
the outcome will be the same.

113
00:06:35,749 --> 00:06:38,569
I don't know how
Kenshin stays so cool.

114
00:06:38,569 --> 00:06:39,729
He's the best
warrior I've ever seen.

115
00:06:39,729 --> 00:06:42,689
But this kid, Sojiro,
moves like he's possessed.

116
00:06:42,689 --> 00:06:43,689
If it was me standing there,

117
00:06:43,689 --> 00:06:45,709
I don't think
I could act so confident.

118
00:06:45,709 --> 00:06:48,499
He must see something I don't.

119
00:06:48,499 --> 00:06:51,589
To me, this kid's
as lethal as a snake.

120
00:06:51,589 --> 00:06:53,599
You're supposed to be good,

121
00:06:53,599 --> 00:06:55,759
but I'm younger
and my reflexes are faster.

122
00:06:55,759 --> 00:06:56,789
That's life,

123
00:06:56,789 --> 00:06:59,569
or, in your case, that's death.

124
00:06:59,569 --> 00:07:01,529
No one maintains
their edge forever.

125
00:07:01,529 --> 00:07:04,559
It's time to retire,
you old man.

126
00:07:04,559 --> 00:07:06,579
I see.

127
00:07:06,579 --> 00:07:07,749
Well, in that case.

128
00:07:07,749 --> 00:07:09,619
I won't be needing this.

129
00:07:09,619 --> 00:07:13,739
♪

130
00:07:13,739 --> 00:07:15,499
He's not giving up.

131
00:07:15,499 --> 00:07:16,619
He's positioning himself.

132
00:07:16,619 --> 00:07:19,579
Yes, he's going to pull
his sword Batto style.

133
00:07:19,579 --> 00:07:20,759
(unintelligible).

134
00:07:20,759 --> 00:07:23,579
There's only one strategy
he could be planning.

135
00:07:23,579 --> 00:07:24,789
He's gonna try and
fake the kid out.

136
00:07:24,789 --> 00:07:29,649
♪

137
00:07:29,649 --> 00:07:31,599
So come on.

138
00:07:31,599 --> 00:07:32,599
That's it?

139
00:07:32,599 --> 00:07:33,719
Why are you surprised?

140
00:07:33,719 --> 00:07:34,669
You're right.

141
00:07:34,669 --> 00:07:36,719
I can't live forever.

142
00:07:36,719 --> 00:07:39,589
All I can say is,
whatever you're gonna do

143
00:07:39,589 --> 00:07:40,709
make it quick.

144
00:07:40,709 --> 00:07:44,609
Let's see if you're
really as good as you claim.

145
00:07:44,609 --> 00:07:45,679
Believe me, I am.

146
00:07:45,679 --> 00:07:48,719
I respect your courage
in accepting the inevitable.

147
00:07:48,719 --> 00:07:51,729
He really thinks
Kenshin's giving up.

148
00:07:51,729 --> 00:07:54,509
He's got to learn.

149
00:07:54,509 --> 00:07:55,689
It's the only way.

150
00:07:55,689 --> 00:07:58,549
There is much about
Mr. Himura that I admire,

151
00:07:58,549 --> 00:08:01,749
but the old must
make way for the new.

152
00:08:01,749 --> 00:08:05,589
His oath not to kill again
proves that he's weak.

153
00:08:05,589 --> 00:08:07,619
It's just as Mr. Shishio says,

154
00:08:07,619 --> 00:08:10,549
only the strong survive.

155
00:08:10,549 --> 00:08:13,549
Himura's death will prove
he was right all along.

156
00:08:13,549 --> 00:08:16,589
♪

157
00:08:16,589 --> 00:08:17,659
It's showtime.

158
00:08:17,659 --> 00:08:19,769
♪

159
00:08:19,769 --> 00:08:21,539
His speed's amazing.

160
00:08:21,539 --> 00:08:23,659
I can't follow him.

161
00:08:23,659 --> 00:08:24,749
Himura's just as fast.

162
00:08:24,749 --> 00:08:27,509
I knew Kenshin would fight back.

163
00:08:27,509 --> 00:08:29,689
I only hope
his strategy pays off.

164
00:08:29,689 --> 00:08:32,689
(screaming)

165
00:08:32,689 --> 00:08:34,689
♪

166
00:08:34,689 --> 00:08:37,689
(sharp ringing)

167
00:08:37,689 --> 00:08:45,669
♪

168
00:08:50,709 --> 00:08:52,519
Are you all right, Kenshin?

169
00:08:52,519 --> 00:08:55,499
(gasping)

170
00:08:59,749 --> 00:09:02,569
What about Sojiro?

171
00:09:02,569 --> 00:09:03,539
(grunts)

172
00:09:12,499 --> 00:09:17,559
I guess my technique
isn't as good as I thought.

173
00:09:17,559 --> 00:09:22,629
Perhaps my philosophy
is flawed, as well.

174
00:09:22,629 --> 00:09:26,559
I can't believe that
a man devoted to nonviolence

175
00:09:26,559 --> 00:09:27,769
could be this strong against me

176
00:09:27,769 --> 00:09:30,739
in a face off, one-to-one.

177
00:09:30,739 --> 00:09:35,519
Apparently, I've been
wrong about everything.

178
00:09:35,519 --> 00:09:36,739
Don't say that.

179
00:09:36,739 --> 00:09:38,519
It's not true.

180
00:09:38,519 --> 00:09:41,629
A building's only as
strong as its foundation,

181
00:09:41,629 --> 00:09:44,669
and mine is real defective.

182
00:09:44,669 --> 00:09:46,499
I see it clearly now.

183
00:09:46,499 --> 00:09:49,699
Real strength doesn't come
from your ability with a weapon.

184
00:09:49,699 --> 00:09:52,579
It comes from being true
to your inner voice.

185
00:09:52,579 --> 00:09:54,619
I ignored that inner voice

186
00:09:54,619 --> 00:09:55,719
all these years,

187
00:09:55,719 --> 00:09:58,699
and now I have to pay a price.

188
00:09:58,699 --> 00:10:03,559
I guess I'll have to find
the path to start over.

189
00:10:03,559 --> 00:10:05,719
Will you act as
my guide, Mr. Himura?

190
00:10:05,719 --> 00:10:08,529
♪

191
00:10:08,529 --> 00:10:10,499
I'm sorry, Sojiro.

192
00:10:10,499 --> 00:10:11,749
It's not as simple
as having someone tell you

193
00:10:11,749 --> 00:10:14,509
this is right or that is wrong.

194
00:10:14,509 --> 00:10:17,609
That's how you got in
trouble in the first place.

195
00:10:17,609 --> 00:10:19,689
You see now that the toughest
warriors in this life

196
00:10:19,689 --> 00:10:22,659
are not necessarily the ones
with the greatest strength

197
00:10:22,659 --> 00:10:25,659
or even the ones
with the fastest reflexes.

198
00:10:25,659 --> 00:10:27,499
The toughest warriors

199
00:10:27,499 --> 00:10:29,569
are those who have the willpower
to put down their swords

200
00:10:29,569 --> 00:10:30,749
and find a more
constructive answer

201
00:10:30,749 --> 00:10:32,609
to life's challenges.

202
00:10:32,609 --> 00:10:34,599
I can't provide that answer.

203
00:10:34,599 --> 00:10:35,789
You'll discover it for yourself

204
00:10:35,789 --> 00:10:37,639
as you make your way
in the world.

205
00:10:37,639 --> 00:10:41,619
♪

206
00:10:41,619 --> 00:10:42,769
Like you did.

207
00:10:42,769 --> 00:10:44,679
I understand, Kenshin.

208
00:10:44,679 --> 00:10:49,719
♪

209
00:10:49,719 --> 00:10:52,619
You will be my role model.

210
00:10:52,619 --> 00:10:54,639
(whimpering)

211
00:10:54,639 --> 00:10:57,569
I promise I'll do my best.

212
00:10:57,569 --> 00:11:00,559
Someday I hope
you will be proud of me.

213
00:11:00,559 --> 00:11:01,759
But more than that,

214
00:11:01,759 --> 00:11:03,679
I hope I'll be proud of me.

215
00:11:03,679 --> 00:11:05,719
I have a feeling you will.

216
00:11:05,719 --> 00:11:07,141
♪

217
00:11:18,659 --> 00:11:21,629
(panting)

218
00:11:27,629 --> 00:11:30,759
(grunting)

219
00:11:30,759 --> 00:11:33,689
Hey, you don't
look so good, Aoshi.

220
00:11:33,689 --> 00:11:34,150
Who's there?

221
00:11:34,150 --> 00:11:34,749
Saito?

222
00:11:34,749 --> 00:11:37,589
♪

223
00:11:37,589 --> 00:11:40,589
I haven't seen you since
that time at the Kamiya dojo.

224
00:11:40,589 --> 00:11:41,659
Just what do you want?

225
00:11:41,659 --> 00:11:44,679
Battousai isn't here,
he left a long time ago.

226
00:11:44,679 --> 00:11:45,739
That's a filthy habit.

227
00:11:45,739 --> 00:11:46,689
I thought you were
going to fight him

228
00:11:46,689 --> 00:11:49,649
in a final confrontation.

229
00:11:49,649 --> 00:11:51,639
Oh, I will fight him
and beat him.

230
00:11:51,639 --> 00:11:54,579
In fact, everything's
proceeding according to plan.

231
00:11:54,579 --> 00:11:55,779
What do you mean?

232
00:11:55,779 --> 00:12:02,629
♪

233
00:12:02,629 --> 00:12:04,789
Why, this is a blueprint
of Shishio's hideout.

234
00:12:04,789 --> 00:12:06,699
How did you get this?

235
00:12:06,699 --> 00:12:07,689
Oh, come now, Aoshi.

236
00:12:07,689 --> 00:12:08,699
I have my ways.

237
00:12:08,699 --> 00:12:10,669
The Oni gang isn't
the only organization

238
00:12:10,669 --> 00:12:12,689
with intelligence-
gathering capabilities.

239
00:12:12,689 --> 00:12:14,569
It's our business
to know what's happening.

240
00:12:14,569 --> 00:12:17,559
That's why I'm a member
of the secret police.

241
00:12:17,559 --> 00:12:18,579
Once Battousai leads us

242
00:12:18,579 --> 00:12:20,639
to the location
and eliminates Shishio,

243
00:12:20,639 --> 00:12:23,679
we'll move in and destroy
what's left of his gang.

244
00:12:23,679 --> 00:12:24,719
So you're going to use Battousai

245
00:12:24,719 --> 00:12:26,519
to do your dirty work,

246
00:12:26,519 --> 00:12:28,729
so you can step up
and claim all the glory.

247
00:12:28,729 --> 00:12:30,539
Yeah.

248
00:12:30,539 --> 00:12:31,669
That's pretty much how it'll go.

249
00:12:31,669 --> 00:12:33,519
There's only one problem.

250
00:12:33,519 --> 00:12:34,739
You've wanted to have
a final confrontation

251
00:12:34,739 --> 00:12:36,759
with Battousai yourself.

252
00:12:36,759 --> 00:12:38,569
How will that ever get resolved

253
00:12:38,569 --> 00:12:42,549
if he loses the fight
with Shishio and gets killed?

254
00:12:42,549 --> 00:12:43,729
Hmm...in that case,

255
00:12:43,729 --> 00:12:45,719
I suppose I'll have
to beat Shishio myself,

256
00:12:45,719 --> 00:12:47,609
and as the last man standing,

257
00:12:47,609 --> 00:12:49,539
obviously I'll be the winner.

258
00:12:49,539 --> 00:12:51,679
Thanks to your continuing
battles with Battousai,

259
00:12:51,679 --> 00:12:54,529
I'm in a position to take
advantage of that opportunity

260
00:12:54,529 --> 00:12:56,629
if and when the time comes.

261
00:12:56,629 --> 00:12:58,549
See you around.

262
00:12:58,549 --> 00:13:00,579
What a slime bucket
you are, Saito.

263
00:13:00,579 --> 00:13:02,629
You know you can't defeat
Battousai head-to-head,

264
00:13:02,629 --> 00:13:04,759
so you set it up for
someone else to step in

265
00:13:04,759 --> 00:13:06,749
and take care of him for you.

266
00:13:06,749 --> 00:13:08,649
It's just the kind
of low-life strategy

267
00:13:08,649 --> 00:13:12,569
I'd expect from the former
head of the Shinsen patrol.

268
00:13:12,569 --> 00:13:14,519
But you may have
outsmarted yourself.

269
00:13:14,519 --> 00:13:16,699
I'll put my money on
Battousai against Shishio,

270
00:13:16,699 --> 00:13:18,729
and when he finally
does face you,

271
00:13:18,729 --> 00:13:22,529
we'll see what kind
of man you really are.

272
00:13:22,529 --> 00:13:24,789
(footsteps pounding)

273
00:13:24,789 --> 00:13:26,649
You think Sojiro
will be all right?

274
00:13:26,649 --> 00:13:28,539
Yeah, those were
superficial wounds.

275
00:13:28,539 --> 00:13:30,519
His life's not really in danger.

276
00:13:30,519 --> 00:13:32,649
I'm not talking
about his wounds, Sano.

277
00:13:32,649 --> 00:13:33,709
I know, I really think

278
00:13:33,709 --> 00:13:35,619
you did the kid
a big favor, Kenshin.

279
00:13:35,619 --> 00:13:36,759
He would have
ended up as a street thug

280
00:13:36,759 --> 00:13:38,699
if you hadn't stepped in.

281
00:13:38,699 --> 00:13:39,759
♪

282
00:13:39,759 --> 00:13:41,549
At least now he has a future

283
00:13:41,549 --> 00:13:43,559
if he can resist Shishio.

284
00:13:43,559 --> 00:13:44,689
That's the question, isn't it?

285
00:13:44,689 --> 00:13:47,519
Does he have the strength
to cut those ties?

286
00:13:47,519 --> 00:13:50,629
♪

287
00:13:50,629 --> 00:13:53,759
Sojiro, I have to go.

288
00:13:53,759 --> 00:13:54,759
Are you feeling well enough

289
00:13:54,759 --> 00:13:56,729
to get along by yourself?

290
00:13:56,729 --> 00:13:58,569
Yes, I'm all right,

291
00:13:58,569 --> 00:13:59,759
but I want you to do me a favor.

292
00:13:59,759 --> 00:14:01,639
Go through the secret
passage in back,

293
00:14:01,639 --> 00:14:03,639
and give Shishio
a message from me.

294
00:14:03,639 --> 00:14:06,569
It's about the way Himura
sets up for an attack.

295
00:14:06,569 --> 00:14:08,519
I hope it saves his life.

296
00:14:08,519 --> 00:14:11,779
It's the least I can do
after what he's done for me.

297
00:14:11,779 --> 00:14:13,579
It's an easy tip.

298
00:14:13,579 --> 00:14:15,529
When they fight,
tell him to keep an eye

299
00:14:15,529 --> 00:14:16,539
on Himura's left foot.

300
00:14:16,539 --> 00:14:18,609
I'm sorry, Sojiro,
I don't understand.

301
00:14:18,609 --> 00:14:20,609
♪

302
00:14:20,609 --> 00:14:23,579
The left foot?

303
00:14:23,579 --> 00:14:24,549
Yes.

304
00:14:24,549 --> 00:14:25,729
It's so obvious.

305
00:14:25,729 --> 00:14:29,519
I wish I'd reacted faster.

306
00:14:29,519 --> 00:14:30,599
Oh, well.

307
00:14:30,599 --> 00:14:36,519
♪

308
00:14:36,519 --> 00:14:38,709
-He led with his left foot?
-Mm-hm.

309
00:14:38,709 --> 00:14:41,549
The Batto fight technique
can be very complex,

310
00:14:41,549 --> 00:14:43,539
but there's
a reason for every move.

311
00:14:43,539 --> 00:14:44,499
When pulling your sword,

312
00:14:44,499 --> 00:14:45,729
you usually put
your right leg forward,

313
00:14:45,729 --> 00:14:47,769
so you don't
accidentally cut yourself.

314
00:14:47,769 --> 00:14:51,499
But Himura put his
left leg forward instead.

315
00:14:51,499 --> 00:14:52,649
And he added a little twist,

316
00:14:52,649 --> 00:14:54,749
so that not only would
he avoid cutting his leg,

317
00:14:54,749 --> 00:14:57,639
he would also increase
his acceleration and weight.

318
00:14:57,639 --> 00:14:59,579
It's a brilliant improvisation.

319
00:14:59,579 --> 00:15:03,499
It must have taken him
years to perfect it.

320
00:15:03,499 --> 00:15:06,569
It increases his speed
by a factor of ten.

321
00:15:06,569 --> 00:15:07,699
No way.

322
00:15:07,699 --> 00:15:08,729
In just one step?

323
00:15:08,729 --> 00:15:10,599
Oh, yes.

324
00:15:10,599 --> 00:15:13,539
But that one step
is hard to accomplish.

325
00:15:13,539 --> 00:15:15,699
The correct state of mind
is very important.

326
00:15:15,699 --> 00:15:18,549
If you don't have a
positive attitude about life,

327
00:15:18,549 --> 00:15:19,729
you won't be able to do it.

328
00:15:19,729 --> 00:15:21,759
Believe me, I know
what I'm talking about.

329
00:15:21,759 --> 00:15:23,749
I tried for years
to incorporate that move,

330
00:15:23,749 --> 00:15:26,619
but something inside of me
just kept resisting it.

331
00:15:26,619 --> 00:15:28,639
Deep down, I never
had enough confidence.

332
00:15:28,639 --> 00:15:29,609
Really?

333
00:15:29,609 --> 00:15:30,739
But you were able to determine

334
00:15:30,739 --> 00:15:32,789
when Himura was about to do it.

335
00:15:32,789 --> 00:15:34,659
So you're warning Shishio?

336
00:15:34,659 --> 00:15:35,649
(grunts)

337
00:15:35,649 --> 00:15:37,729
Just think of it as
my farewell gift to him.

338
00:15:37,729 --> 00:15:40,669
I don't want him to get hurt
when he fights Battousai.

339
00:15:40,669 --> 00:15:41,699
So listen,

340
00:15:41,699 --> 00:15:44,499
Himura's eyes and arms
are not important here.

341
00:15:44,499 --> 00:15:45,499
He can't make this move

342
00:15:45,499 --> 00:15:47,579
without first putting
his left foot forward.

343
00:15:47,579 --> 00:15:48,789
When Shishio sees
that happening,

344
00:15:48,789 --> 00:15:51,659
he should be able
to anticipate the maneuver.

345
00:15:51,659 --> 00:15:54,589
I'd better go warn Shishio now.

346
00:15:54,589 --> 00:15:56,509
Hold on a minute, Yumi.

347
00:15:56,509 --> 00:15:57,709
I know you're in a hurry,

348
00:15:57,709 --> 00:16:00,589
but I have one more
favor to ask of you.

349
00:16:04,509 --> 00:16:05,599
It's beautiful.

350
00:16:05,599 --> 00:16:07,749
♪

351
00:16:07,749 --> 00:16:11,569
It's the sword Mr. Shishio
gave me a long time ago.

352
00:16:11,569 --> 00:16:12,639
It's precious to me.

353
00:16:12,639 --> 00:16:15,539
It's been my treasure
for the last ten years,

354
00:16:15,539 --> 00:16:17,669
but now it's time
to return this sword

355
00:16:17,669 --> 00:16:18,719
to its rightful owner.

356
00:16:18,719 --> 00:16:20,509
Sojiro.

357
00:16:20,509 --> 00:16:21,689
He'd want you to keep it.

358
00:16:21,689 --> 00:16:23,789
When I was about to be
killed a few years back.

359
00:16:23,789 --> 00:16:26,759
Mr. Shishio stepped in
with this sword to protect me.

360
00:16:26,759 --> 00:16:28,659
I'll never forget that.

361
00:16:28,659 --> 00:16:30,599
He gave me my life.

362
00:16:30,599 --> 00:16:31,719
♪

363
00:16:31,719 --> 00:16:33,729
Now I'm about
to betray that loyalty

364
00:16:33,729 --> 00:16:36,729
by deserting him at the moment
when he needs me most.

365
00:16:36,729 --> 00:16:39,509
I'm going off to find
the truth of my life,

366
00:16:39,509 --> 00:16:41,629
just as Mr. Himura suggested.

367
00:16:41,629 --> 00:16:42,789
Do you understand, Yumi?

368
00:16:42,789 --> 00:16:44,579
I can't keep this sword.

369
00:16:44,579 --> 00:16:45,689
I can't.

370
00:16:45,689 --> 00:16:46,779
I have to be free.

371
00:16:46,779 --> 00:16:51,559
♪

372
00:16:51,559 --> 00:16:52,739
I see.

373
00:16:52,739 --> 00:16:54,559
I'll tell Shishio.

374
00:16:54,559 --> 00:16:55,639
For now, this is something

375
00:16:55,639 --> 00:16:57,519
you have to do.

376
00:16:57,519 --> 00:16:59,789
♪

377
00:16:59,789 --> 00:17:02,619
Thank you for understanding.

378
00:17:02,619 --> 00:17:03,779
Don't let anyone hurt him.

379
00:17:03,779 --> 00:17:05,609
It's all right, don't worry.

380
00:17:05,609 --> 00:17:07,549
He really doesn't
need protection.

381
00:17:07,549 --> 00:17:09,509
He's stronger than both of us.

382
00:17:09,509 --> 00:17:10,789
That's not what I meant.

383
00:17:10,789 --> 00:17:12,539
Ah.

384
00:17:12,539 --> 00:17:13,639
I get it now.

385
00:17:13,639 --> 00:17:15,649
♪

386
00:17:15,649 --> 00:17:16,719
Goodbye.

387
00:17:16,719 --> 00:17:18,539
Take care of yourself.

388
00:17:18,539 --> 00:17:19,599
(door sliding)

389
00:17:19,599 --> 00:17:35,549
♪

390
00:17:35,549 --> 00:17:37,649
Goodbye, Mr. Shishio.

391
00:17:37,649 --> 00:17:40,619
(rain falling)

392
00:17:44,759 --> 00:17:46,719
That's what he said?

393
00:17:46,719 --> 00:17:48,649
It's a farewell gift?

394
00:17:48,649 --> 00:17:50,609
He must have been
too ashamed to face me

395
00:17:50,609 --> 00:17:52,629
after he lost to Himura.

396
00:17:52,629 --> 00:17:54,699
I should have anticipated this.

397
00:17:54,699 --> 00:17:56,609
Ah, it's obvious

398
00:17:56,609 --> 00:17:59,659
I'm the only one
who can defeat Battousai.

399
00:17:59,659 --> 00:18:01,709
All right, I'm
ready to face him.

400
00:18:01,709 --> 00:18:03,679
If I hadn't done
this in the first place,

401
00:18:03,679 --> 00:18:05,729
we wouldn't be in this position.

402
00:18:05,729 --> 00:18:07,569
I don't know how
Battousai does it,

403
00:18:07,569 --> 00:18:09,549
since he's vowed
not to kill anyone.

404
00:18:09,549 --> 00:18:10,769
But I'm not restricted
by such an oath.

405
00:18:10,769 --> 00:18:11,789
And when this battle's over,

406
00:18:11,789 --> 00:18:13,569
nothing will stand in the way

407
00:18:13,569 --> 00:18:15,659
of our complete domination
of this country.

408
00:18:15,659 --> 00:18:17,649
We'll be the masters of Japan.

409
00:18:17,649 --> 00:18:19,709
Facing Battousai
has got me as excited

410
00:18:19,709 --> 00:18:22,729
as taking over this government!

411
00:18:22,729 --> 00:18:24,789
Yes, I share your enthusiasm,

412
00:18:24,789 --> 00:18:26,649
but we have practical problems.

413
00:18:26,649 --> 00:18:28,659
Most of our soldiers
have been arrested.

414
00:18:28,659 --> 00:18:30,769
And the Juppongatana
has almost been destroyed.

415
00:18:30,769 --> 00:18:32,519
In assessing the damage,

416
00:18:32,519 --> 00:18:33,569
it appears that our timetable

417
00:18:33,569 --> 00:18:35,729
has been set back
by a number of years.

418
00:18:35,729 --> 00:18:37,539
Don't be so concerned.

419
00:18:37,539 --> 00:18:39,569
Yes, we've lost a few battles,

420
00:18:39,569 --> 00:18:41,679
but as long as I'm alive,
we're in business.

421
00:18:41,679 --> 00:18:43,699
Ahhh!

422
00:18:43,699 --> 00:18:44,749
He's right.

423
00:18:44,749 --> 00:18:47,559
I don't know why I let
myself get so depressed.

424
00:18:47,559 --> 00:18:49,669
He's the most brilliant
tactician I've ever seen!

425
00:18:49,669 --> 00:18:51,749
Always a step ahead
of his enemies.

426
00:18:51,749 --> 00:18:53,789
If he said he could make
the sun rise in the west,

427
00:18:53,789 --> 00:18:55,539
I'd believe it!

428
00:18:55,539 --> 00:18:57,539
This country needs
a strong leader,

429
00:18:57,539 --> 00:18:59,689
and no one is more
qualified than Shishio.

430
00:18:59,689 --> 00:19:02,569
I'll do whatever it takes
to put him in power.

431
00:19:02,569 --> 00:19:04,639
I swear it!

432
00:19:04,639 --> 00:19:06,509
(running and panting)

433
00:19:06,509 --> 00:19:07,609
It's a dead end!

434
00:19:07,609 --> 00:19:08,769
This must be
Shishio's stronghold.

435
00:19:08,769 --> 00:19:10,759
Stay with me, Kenshin,
'cause I'm breaking on through

436
00:19:10,759 --> 00:19:12,679
to the other side.

437
00:19:12,679 --> 00:19:15,769
(screaming)

438
00:19:15,769 --> 00:19:19,529
Huh?

439
00:19:19,529 --> 00:19:20,719
I've been waiting for you.

440
00:19:20,719 --> 00:19:22,499
What was the big delay?

441
00:19:22,499 --> 00:19:24,559
Ah, how'd you get here so fast?

442
00:19:24,559 --> 00:19:27,629
Mr. Shishio says he'll meet
you both in the fighting room.

443
00:19:27,629 --> 00:19:28,639
Come along with me.

444
00:19:28,639 --> 00:19:29,599
Well, that's perfect, lady,

445
00:19:29,599 --> 00:19:31,649
'cause that's
exactly why we're here.

446
00:19:31,649 --> 00:19:32,719
You ready to face him?

447
00:19:32,719 --> 00:19:34,539
Yeah.

448
00:19:34,539 --> 00:19:35,559
All right, then.

449
00:19:35,559 --> 00:19:36,709
(groans)

450
00:19:36,709 --> 00:19:37,679
What's that?

451
00:19:37,679 --> 00:19:39,569
I'm okay, don't worry.

452
00:19:39,569 --> 00:19:40,549
Let's go get him.

453
00:19:41,739 --> 00:19:43,749
Maybe you'd like
to meet some other time?

454
00:19:43,749 --> 00:19:44,769
What?!

455
00:19:44,769 --> 00:19:47,649
After all, you've had
a couple of major fights today.

456
00:19:47,649 --> 00:19:49,769
I'm just saying that you
might not be at your best.

457
00:19:49,769 --> 00:19:51,529
He's all right.

458
00:19:51,529 --> 00:19:52,579
I'll make you a deal.

459
00:19:52,579 --> 00:19:53,719
You can leave if you want to,

460
00:19:53,719 --> 00:19:56,689
just promise me you'll
leave Mr. Shishio alone.

461
00:19:56,689 --> 00:19:58,639
I'll tell him you
couldn't find the hideout,

462
00:19:58,639 --> 00:20:00,629
got discouraged, and went home.

463
00:20:00,629 --> 00:20:01,509
Think about it.

464
00:20:01,509 --> 00:20:02,649
It's not a bad offer.

465
00:20:02,649 --> 00:20:03,719
Everyone saves face,

466
00:20:03,719 --> 00:20:06,629
and you can fight later
if you're up to it.

467
00:20:06,629 --> 00:20:08,619
Thank you, Yumi.

468
00:20:08,619 --> 00:20:09,709
You're a very caring person.

469
00:20:09,709 --> 00:20:13,579
♪

470
00:20:13,579 --> 00:20:14,559
I can see you're worried

471
00:20:14,559 --> 00:20:16,589
about the outcome
of this battle.

472
00:20:16,589 --> 00:20:19,539
After all, Mr. Shishio could
very well lose his life.

473
00:20:19,539 --> 00:20:20,689
He's a very lucky man.

474
00:20:20,689 --> 00:20:22,569
Not everyone has
a guardian angel

475
00:20:22,569 --> 00:20:25,569
so vigilantly
watching over them.

476
00:20:25,569 --> 00:20:29,519
Hm, you're shortsighted
and stupid, Himura.

477
00:20:29,519 --> 00:20:30,719
You could lose, you know.

478
00:20:32,579 --> 00:20:34,619
♪

479
00:20:34,619 --> 00:20:35,749
-You ready?
-Uh-huh.

480
00:20:35,749 --> 00:20:37,569
Don't forget what I said.

481
00:20:37,569 --> 00:20:38,749
This is gonna be
a fight to the finish

482
00:20:38,749 --> 00:20:40,739
between me and Shishio.

483
00:20:40,739 --> 00:20:42,769
No matter what happens,
I don't want you to interfere.

484
00:20:42,769 --> 00:20:44,619
You understand?

485
00:20:44,619 --> 00:20:46,569
♪

486
00:20:46,569 --> 00:20:48,609
-All right?
-All right.

487
00:20:48,609 --> 00:20:50,669
Whatever you say.

488
00:20:50,669 --> 00:20:51,649
You're a good friend.

489
00:20:51,649 --> 00:20:53,769
♪

490
00:20:53,769 --> 00:20:55,669
But no matter what I promised,

491
00:20:55,669 --> 00:20:57,749
I'm not gonna let you die here.

492
00:20:57,749 --> 00:21:00,519
I wouldn't be able to live
with myself otherwise.

493
00:21:00,519 --> 00:21:02,679
Yoshi and Kori
need you too much,

494
00:21:02,679 --> 00:21:04,499
and they're not the only ones.

495
00:21:04,499 --> 00:21:05,689
There are a lot
of people in this country

496
00:21:05,689 --> 00:21:08,619
who depend on you
for guidance and protection.

497
00:21:08,619 --> 00:21:09,709
Call me what you like.

498
00:21:09,709 --> 00:21:11,729
If I feel you're in danger
of losing your life,

499
00:21:11,729 --> 00:21:14,539
I'm gonna step in and save you.

500
00:21:14,539 --> 00:21:15,659
There's too much at stake.

501
00:21:15,659 --> 00:21:16,789
That's my vow, Kenshin,

502
00:21:16,789 --> 00:21:19,779
and I will put everything
I've got behind it.

503
00:21:19,779 --> 00:21:37,769
♪

504
00:21:37,769 --> 00:21:40,739
(pocket watch ticking)

505
00:21:43,499 --> 00:21:44,769
(echoing thud)

506
00:21:48,639 --> 00:21:50,559
This is as far as I can go.

507
00:21:50,559 --> 00:21:52,629
Behind this door
is a fighting arena.

508
00:21:52,629 --> 00:21:54,719
It's where Shishio's
been waiting for you.

509
00:21:54,719 --> 00:21:57,639
A final warning, once you
pass through these doors,

510
00:21:57,639 --> 00:21:58,800
there's no escape.

511
00:21:58,800 --> 00:21:59,679
Ready?

512
00:21:59,679 --> 00:22:02,559
♪

513
00:22:02,559 --> 00:22:04,559
(chain rattling)

514
00:22:04,559 --> 00:22:43,509
♪

515
00:22:43,509 --> 00:22:45,719
(laughing maniacally)

516
00:22:47,499 --> 00:23:10,699
♪

517
00:23:10,699 --> 00:23:12,699
(singing in foreign language)

518
00:23:12,699 --> 00:25:05,729
♪

